The '''Nevelo''' is a tram designed by [[Newag]] and built in its [[Nowy S<U+0105>cz]] factory.

==History==
In May 2013, the first complete tram was taken to [[Krak<U+00F3>w]] for trial running.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://infotram.pl/text.php?from=search&id=55599|title=Tramwaj Newagu jest ju<U+017C> w Krakowie|date=7 May 2013|work=Infotram|accessdate=1 July 2013}}</ref>

==Technology==
The Nevelo is a three-section, articulated, 100% low-floor tram. It has space for 60 seated passengers and 175 standing. The Nevelo has several features designed to lower operating costs, such as regeneration with supercapacitor energy storage. The wheels and suspension are claimed to reduce wear. Wide doors and ramps are provided, to improve wheelchair accessibility.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.railwaygazette.com/news/urban/single-view/view/newag-tram-rolls-onto-the-streets-of-krakow.html|accessdate=1 July 2013|title=Newag tram rolls onto the streets of Krak<U+00F3>w|work=[[Railway Gazette International]]}}</ref>

